<section id="about" class="section wrap" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
  <h2 id="about-heading" class="section-title">About</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I work on problems where <strong>data, money, and global scale</strong> intersect
      — streaming and batch pipelines, long-running workflow orchestration, and
      systems that must remain consistent across regions under real-world failure
      conditions.
    </p>
    <p>
      At Amazon, I’ve spent <strong>9+ years</strong> building and operating distributed
      systems across services like <strong>Bedrock</strong> and
      <strong>Kinesis Video Streams</strong>. My current work focuses on metering,
      allocation, and settlement pipelines powering generative AI platforms — where
      correctness, latency, and operational clarity are critical.
    </p>
    <p>
      I spend a lot of time on <strong>architecture reviews, system design, and
      mentoring</strong>, turning ambiguous requirements into systems with clear
      failure modes and measurable behavior.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of work, I’m a parent to a <strong>three-year-old</strong>, a dog person
      (golden retriever, <strong>Splash</strong>), and I recharge with
      <strong>books</strong>, <strong>travel</strong>, and <strong>long walks</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

